description.narrative: Emergency preparedness and response planning was strengthened, alongside humanitarian action capacity enhancement of country office staff, government partners and inter-agency actors, with all (21) countries sustaining compliance against UNICEF global procedures and increasing focus on operational aspects (contingency planning; shock responsive systems; requisite partnerships). Risk monitoring was strengthened through regular dissemination of region-wide risk analysis and establishment of a monitoring system for refugee/migrant movements in 10 countries. In terms of disaster risk reduction (DRR) an important sub-regional partnership was advanced with IFRC to support earthquake preparedness for Central Asia. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
